of Collaborative Consumption. When I got the
blurb for this book, I was really excited.

00:00:10.420 --> 00:00:18.100
Then I saw Rachel's TED Talk and I was even
more excited. She was a fantastic speaker

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:22.039
there and I expect her to be a fantastic speaker
and then I read the book; loved the book.

00:00:22.039 --> 00:00:28.759
In fact, I've been, evangelized everybody
on my Facebook page to on my Buzz, on my,

00:00:28.759 --> 00:00:33.100
talking to my friends in person. My friend's
14 year old kid was super glad to hear about

00:00:33.100 --> 00:00:37.970
share.com cause he's now getting full value
for his video games as opposed to half at

00:00:37.970 --> 00:00:42.470
GameStop. So, it, I think you're gonna find
these ideas super interesting, both personally

00:00:42.470 --> 00:00:46.130
and professionally. I think you know about
some of these companies and I think you're

00:00:46.130 --> 00:00:51.170
gonna find some new companies you haven't
heard of that will be useful to you, but I

00:00:51.170 --> 00:00:54.350
think the book is more than something that's
interesting both personally and professionally.

00:00:54.350 --> 00:00:58.471
It's also a different way of thinking about
the world. It's a way, I said, I think we

00:00:58.471 --> 00:01:03.240
can get by, get past some of the kind of roadblocks
that we've got on public discussions. Because,

00:01:03.240 --> 00:01:08.180
I mean, think about it. Sharing for fun and
profit; what could be more socialist or more

